===Symbol===
'''σ''', '''[[ς]]'''
# The [[lower case]] letter [[sigma]], the 18th letter of the modern [[w:Greek alphabet|Greek alphabet]]. When the final letter in a word of lower case letters is sigma the alternative ('''[[ς]]''') form must be used; it may only be used in this final position.
# (Mathematics & Statistics) The symbol for [[w:Standard deviation|standard deviation]].

'''σ''''
# The number 200 in [[w:Greek numerals|Greek numerals]].

''',σ'''
# The number 200,000 in Greek numerals.

